Q_DESC:
Given an array of N integers, write a program to print K-th distinct element in the array. The given array may contain duplicates and the output should print K-th element among all unique elements. If K is more than number of distinct elements, print -1.

Input:
First line of input contains two space separated integers N and K. Second line of each test case contains N space separated integers.
Output:
Print the K-th distinct element as described above.

Constraints:
1<=N<=100000
1<=K<=100
